title: File:Ny-Ålesund 2013 06 07 3657 (10178803704).jpg
author: Harvey Barrison from Massapequa, NY, USA
description: Ny-Ålesund is one of the four permanent settlements on the island of Spitsbergen in the Svalbard archipelago.  It is one of the world's northernmost functional public settlement at 78°55′N 11°56′E inhabited by a permanent population of approximately 30–35 scientists and support staff
